cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.SD

This paper proposes a novel semi-supervised learning paradigm that addresses label insufficiency and label inaccuracy. The experiments are conducted on image classification, text categorization, and speech recognition, which are all related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves image and speech processing, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SD (Sound) as likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with text categorization, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper involves graph-based methods, which could also suggest cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category.
